From 2ed895f3285c9dd59854aa55ca4ce460bc8ee9a5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 11:48:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] node: fix end-to-end signal-to-wasm pipeline for namespace
 creatures

* appengine
  - Cargo: pin bollard to 0.18 (matches the call sites in
    docker_vm_controller) and add tokio as a direct dependency
  - bootstrap/restore: export restore_previously_running_vms
  - bootstrap/engine: send response payload as bytes (zmq Send needs a
    Sendable, not a String)
  - models/vm_runtime: after commit_as_offchain, re-emit any output the
    creature set via the `output` host op as a `vmOutput` log so the
    host platform can observe what the program produced

* node (Go)
  - chain.RestoreFromStorage: defer chain restore to a public hook the
    Core can call after c.tools is initialised; NewChain ->
    restoreChainsFromStorage -> app.ModifyState used to run before
    c.tools was assigned and dereferenced nil
  - signaler.SignalUser: deliver directly when a VM listener for the
    target ID is registered locally, so program IDs (no User row but
    a VM listener registered via Vmm.Assign) receive signals
  - vmm/hostcall_entities: implement handleStoreCrud for the
    collaboration-Store model (createStore/updateStore/deleteStore/
    getStore/listStores)
  - vmm/hostcall_global: route createStore/updateStore/deleteStore/
    getStore/listStores ops to the new handler; alias output and
    vmOutput to the vm-log handler so creature output is captured
  - actions/creature: dev-mode Firebase bypass when no service-account
    file is present; mirror Creatures to User and Machine tables so
    existing auth/program code paths can find them; resolve the type
    mismatch on /creatures/get from outputs_users.GetOutput to a map
  - actions/program: rename action-path doc comments so secured actions
    actually register under /programs/* (was /machines/* in several
    spots the CLI couldn't reach); save wasm payload as module.wasm
    (not build.sh) and persist vmEntityPath/vmEntityType links so
    resolveVmExecutionTarget can locate the artifact
  - core: serialize access to chainCallbacks/messageCallbacks (concurrent
    map writes were crashing the node); fix base-chain response routing
    to fire the stored callback when the local node was the submitter
    (was comparing against packet.Author, which is user::<id>)
